                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d846">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 <persName corresp="#p_WRACH1"
                        >Woodward</persName> Electoral Mission/165: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-15T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 15, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. Your 175, September 13, 2 p.m. After consultation with this Department the
                    Navy Department, in view of the fact that the Commander of the Guardia states
                    that escort for supplies for the electoral and marine personnel at Matagalpa
                    cannot be furnished by the Guardia, is authorizing the temporary employment of
                    marines to act as escort in this particular instance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
